HEADWORD: Samite
<hw>Sa"mite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>samit</ets>,
LL. <ets>samitum</ets>, <ets>examitum</ets>, from LGr. <?/, <?/ woven
with six threads; Gr. <?/ six + <?/ a thread. See <er>Six</er>, and cf.
<er>Dimity</er>.]</ety> <def>A species of silk stuff, or taffeta,
generally interwoven with gold.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In silken <qex>samite</qex> she was light arrayed.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

